<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        CAB TILTING PROCEDURE - CAB MOUNTING AND TILT MECHANISM
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CAB MOUNTING AND TILT MECHANISM</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The four point mounting used for the cab incorporates the mobility required for tilting. The system
                includes the following: cab front mounting hinges, cab rear mounting pads and latches, and the cab lift
                hydraulic system.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Mounting Hinges</title>
            <para>Two cab front mounting hinges, which the cab lift rams are attached to (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600616">Figure 16</hotlnk>and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600617">Figure 17</hotlnk>), support the front of the cab and permit the cab to tilt
                at this location. The hinges also provide the main disconnect point if the cab must be removed from the
                chassis. The right hinge provides adjustment to square the cab on the chassis.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600616" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600616" filename="../figg16/g1600616.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Cab Left Front Mounting Hinge</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HINGE UPPER HALF</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RAM ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HINGE LOWER HALF</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. PIVOT BOLT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1600617" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600617" filename="../figg16/g1600617.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Cab Right Front Mounting Hinge</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RAM ASSEMBLY AND SAFETY PROP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HINGE UPPER HALF</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. PIVOT BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HINGE LOWER HALF</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
